Put thy conscience to it as thou goest, whether
thou art the man; O happy man, if this be thy case;
But see thou be thorow and impartial in the search.

3. If thy hope be any thing worth, it will purifie thee
from thy sins, 1 Iohn 3. 3. but cursed is that hope,
which doth cherish men in their sins.
